        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks for JSBS’s essays; wishes he had said something on Lister’s observations. Speculates on the fungoid nature of smallpox and why there is seldom re-infection.</p> 
<p>Discusses digestion by <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>, the action of its secretion being the same as that of gastric juice.</p> 
        </abstract>
